name: Garruk Wildspeaker
text: +1: Untap two target lands.\n−1: Put a 3/3 green Beast creature token onto the battlefield.\n−4: Creatures you control get +3/+3 and gain trample until end of turn.

name: Basking Rootwalla
text: {1}{G}: Basking Rootwalla gets +2/+2 until end of turn. Activate this ability only once each turn.\nMadness {0} (If you discard this card, discard it into exile. When you do, cast it for its madness cost or put it into your graveyard.)

name: Albino Troll
text: Echo {1}{G} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\n{1}{G}: Regenerate Albino Troll.

name: Vine Trellis
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Nature twists knots stronger than any rope.

name: Wild Mongrel
text: Discard a card: Wild Mongrel gets +1/+1 and becomes the color of your choice until end of turn.
flavor: It teaches you to play dead.

name: Wirewood Savage
text: Whenever a Beast enters the battlefield, you may draw a card.
flavor: "She is truly Wirewood's child now."\n—Elvish refugee

name: Blastoderm
text: Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nFading 3 (This creature enters the battlefield with three fade counters on it. At the beginning of your upkeep, remove a fade counter from it. If you can't, sacrifice it.)

name: Ravenous Baloth
text: Sacrifice a Beast: You gain 4 life.
flavor: "All we know about the Krosan Forest we have learned from those few who made it out alive."\n—Elvish refugee

name: Stampeding Wildebeests
text: Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, return a green creature you control to its owner's hand.
flavor: The most violent and destructive storms in Femeref occur on cloudless days.

name: Indrik Stomphowler
text: When Indrik Stomphowler enters the battlefield, destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: An indrik's howl has destructive power much subtler than that of its crushing foot.

name: Krosan Tusker
text: Cycling {2}{G} ({2}{G}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Krosan Tusker, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.

name: Plated Slagwurm
text: Hexproof (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities your opponents control.)
flavor: Beneath the Tangle, the wurm tunnels stretch . . . wide as a stone's throw, long as forever, deep as you dare.

name: Genju of the Cedars
text: Enchant Forest\n{2}: Enchanted Forest becomes a 4/4 green Spirit creature until end of turn. It's still a land.\nWhen enchanted Forest is put into a graveyard, you may return Genju of the Cedars from your graveyard to your hand.

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Rancor
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+0 and has trample.\nWhen Rancor is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, return Rancor to its owner's hand.
flavor: Hatred outlives the hateful.

name: Lignify
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature is a Treefolk with base power and toughness 0/4 and loses all abilities.
flavor: Bulgo paused, puzzled. What was that rustling sound, and why did he feel so stiff? And how could his feet be so thirsty?

name: Nature's Lore
text: Search your library for a Forest card and put that card onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Nature's secrets can be read on every tree, every branch, every leaf.

name: Elephant Guide
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +3/+3.\nWhen enchanted creature dies, put a 3/3 green Elephant creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: Nature's strength outlives the strong.

name: Invigorate
text: If you control a Forest, rather than pay Invigorate's mana cost, you may have an opponent gain 3 life.\nTarget creature gets +4/+4 until end of turn.

name: Serrated Arrows
text: Serrated Arrows enters the battlefield with three arrowhead counters on it.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, if there are no arrowhead counters on Serrated Arrows, sacrifice it.\n{T}, Remove an arrowhead counter from Serrated Arrows: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.

name: Harmonize
text: Draw three cards.
flavor: "Words lie. People lie. The land tells the truth."

name: Rude Awakening
text:
Choose one —
• Untap all lands you control.
• Until end of turn, lands you control become 2/2 creatures that are still lands.
Entwine {2}{G} (Choose both if you pay the entwine cost.)

name: Beast Attack
text: Put a 4/4 green Beast creature token onto the battlefield.\nFlashback {2}{G}{G}{G} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

name: Overrun
text: Creatures you control get +3/+3 and gain trample until end of turn.
flavor: Nature doesn't walk.

name: Windstorm
text: Windstorm deals X damage to each creature with flying.
flavor: "We don't like interlopers and thieves cluttering our skies."\n—Dionus, elvish archdruid

name: Slippery Karst
text: Slippery Karst enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Treetop Village
text: Treetop Village enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\n{1}{G}: Treetop Village becomes a 3/3 green Ape creature with trample until end of turn. It's still a land. (If it would assign enough damage to its blockers to destroy them, you may have it assign the rest of its damage to defending player or planeswalker.)

name: Liliana Vess
text: +1: Target player discards a card.\n−2: Search your library for a card, then shuffle your library and put that card on top of it.\n−8: Put all creature cards from all graveyards onto the battlefield under your control.

name: Deathgreeter
text: Whenever another creature dies, you may gain 1 life.
flavor: "The bones of allies grant wisdom. The bones of enemies grant strength. The bones of dragons grant life eternal."

name: Ghost-Lit Stalker
text: {4}{B}, {T}: Target player discards two cards. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery.\nChannel — {5}{B}{B}, Discard Ghost-Lit Stalker: Target player discards four cards. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery.

name: Vampire Bats
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{B}: Vampire Bats gets +1/+0 until end of turn. Activate this ability no more than twice each turn.

name: Drudge Skeletons
text: {B}: Regenerate Drudge Skeletons. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)
flavor: "The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, never surrender, and don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."\n—Nevinyrral, Necromancer's Handbook

name: Ravenous Rats
text: When Ravenous Rats enters the battlefield, target opponent discards a card.
flavor: Nothing is sacred to rats. Everything is simply another meal.

name: Fleshbag Marauder
text: When Fleshbag Marauder enters the battlefield, each player sacrifices a creature.
flavor: Grixis is a world where the only things found in abundance are death and decay. Corpses, whole or in part, are the standard currency among necromancers and demons.

name: Phyrexian Rager
text: When Phyrexian Rager enters the battlefield, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor: It takes no prisoners, but it keeps the choicest bits for Phyrexia.

name: Urborg Syphon-Mage
text: {2}{B}, {T}, Discard a card: Each other player loses 2 life. You gain life equal to the life lost this way.
flavor: "I have become a gourmet of sorts. Each soul has its own distinctive flavor. The art is in inviting the right company to the feast."

name: Wall of Bone
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{B}: Regenerate Wall of Bone. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)
flavor: "Graveyards are sacrilege! A waste of perfectly good bones."\n—Keren-Dur, necromancer lord

name: Faerie Macabre
text: Flying\nDiscard Faerie Macabre: Exile up to two target cards from graveyards.
flavor: The line between dream and death is gauzy and fragile. She leads those too near it from one side to the other.

name: Howling Banshee
text: Flying\nWhen Howling Banshee enters the battlefield, each player loses 3 life.
flavor: Villagers cloaked the town in magical silence, but their ears still bled.

name: Keening Banshee
text: Flying\nWhen Keening Banshee enters the battlefield, target creature gets -2/-2 until end of turn.
flavor: Her cold wail echoes in the alleys and under-eaves, finding the unfortunate and turning their blood to ice.

name: Twisted Abomination
text: {B}: Regenerate Twisted Abomination.\nSwampcycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Search your library for a Swamp card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.)

name: Skeletal Vampire
text:
Flying
When Skeletal Vampire enters the battlefield, put two 1/1 black Bat creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield.
{3}{B}{B}, Sacrifice a Bat: Put two 1/1 black Bat creature tokens with flying onto the battlefield.
Sacrifice a Bat: Regenerate Skeletal Vampire.

name: Genju of the Fens
text: Enchant Swamp\n{2}: Until end of turn, enchanted Swamp becomes a 2/2 black Spirit creature with "{B}: This creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn." It's still a land.\nWhen enchanted Swamp is put into a graveyard, you may return Genju of the Fens from your graveyard to your hand.

name: Bad Moon
text: Black creatures get +1/+1.

name: Sign in Blood
text: Target player draws two cards and loses 2 life.
flavor: "You know I accept only one currency here, and yet you have sought me out. Why now do you hesitate?"\n—Xathrid demon

name: Vicious Hunger
text: Vicious Hunger deals 2 damage to target creature and you gain 2 life.
flavor: Only the most ravenous soul feeds on the health of the weak.

name: Ichor Slick
text: Target creature gets -3/-3 until end of turn.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nMadness {3}{B} (If you discard this card, discard it into exile. When you do, cast it for its madness cost or put it into your graveyard.)

name: Hideous End
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. Its controller loses 2 life.
flavor: "A little dark magic won't stop me. The worse the curse, the better the prize."\n—Radavi, Joraga relic hunter, last words

name: Snuff Out
text: If you control a Swamp, you may pay 4 life rather than pay Snuff Out's mana cost.\nDestroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: "The bigger they are, the faster they rot."

name: Tendrils of Corruption
text: Tendrils of Corruption deals X damage to target creature and you gain X life, where X is the number of Swamps you control.
flavor: Darkness doesn't always send its minions to do its dirty work.

name: Mutilate
text: All creatures get -1/-1 until end of turn for each Swamp you control.
flavor: Liliana developed a fondness for the moment when roaring becomes squealing.

name: Rise from the Grave
text: Put target creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. That creature is a black Zombie in addition to its other colors and types.
flavor: "Death is no excuse for disobedience."\n—Liliana Vess

name: Corrupt
text: Corrupt deals damage equal to the number of Swamps you control to target creature or player. You gain life equal to the damage dealt this way.
flavor: There are things beneath the murk for whom the bog is a stew, a thin broth in need of meat.

name: Enslave
text: Enchant creature\nYou control enchanted creature.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, enchanted creature deals 1 damage to its owner.

name: Polluted Mire
text: Polluted Mire enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {B} to your mana pool.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
